\StemText{
A baker decorates $x$ small cakes and $y$ large cakes.

In one day, he decorates:
\begin{parts}
\item not more than 16 small cakes
\item less than 10 large cakes
\item more small cakes than large cakes
\item a total of not more than 24 cakes.
\end{parts}

One of the inequalities that shows this information is $x \leqslant 16$.

\begin{parts}

\part Write down the other three inequalities in $x$ and/or $y$.

\AnswerLine[.......................][][][3]
\Marks{3}

\part On the grid, draw four straight lines and shade the unwanted regions to show these inequalities.

Label the region, R, which satisfies the four inequalities.

\begin{center}
\relinput{Figures/Q08b-CoordinateGrid.tex}
\end{center}
\Marks{6}

\part The baker earns \$8 for decorating a small cake and \$12 for decorating a large cake.

Use your diagram to find the largest amount the baker can earn in one day by decorating cakes.
\AnswerLine[][\$]
\Marks{2}

\end{parts}
}

